Office of Monsieur Pujol,
...yes?.

50
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:28,673
 Mademoiselle Nadège,

51
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:31,838
Madame Pujol here.
Oh, hello, Madame Pujol.

52
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:36,158
My husband got home late last
night from the 'Bada-Boom' with the German

53
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:38,749
and this morning
he forgot to take his drops.

54
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:41,918
So if you'd tell him to drop back home,
as soon as he gets in.

55
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:43,878
I couldn't do that ...

56
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:46,719
You know the state he gets
in when he doesn't take them

57
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:50,196
Can I count on you?
I'll tell him.

58
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,670
Thanks. Goodbye.

59
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,996
A good deed done.

60
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,672
Good morning, sir.
What else?

61
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,632
I'd like a word with you.

62
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,956
You already on a
cigarette break?

63
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,912
Excuse us, Monsieur Pujol.

64
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,516
'Morning Nadège.
Your wife called.

65
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,551
What does she want?
"Your drops."

66
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,910
Aagh... she pisses me off!

67
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,998
No touching.
What?

68
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,077
What's this story about a German?

69
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,794
I'll explain.
No need. Keep that for your wife.

70
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:52,231
You're not gonna make a scene.
Tomorrow night ...

71
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,590
You'll go back to
the 'Bada-Boom'.

72
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,677
It's closed on Thursdays.

73
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,115
Mama, are you there?

74
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:19,999
Joel! Hello darling.

75
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,634
Happy birthday... I just picked it for you.
Oh, thank you.

76
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:25,400
How thoughtful.
You're up early.

77
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,790
I dropped the children at school.
Are they well?

78
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,713
Yes, but they're upset 
their father's away.

79
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,831
Give me a hand.
You've heard from him?

80
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:36,038
Jean-Charles finally phoned me
from Toronto.

81
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,838
Things going well?

82
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,548
Certainly...
I think we'll separate.

83
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,916
What?

84
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:46,152
He travels all the time,
we never see him.

85
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:49,557
I feel he's not
interested in me any more.

86
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,916
You should go with him on his trips.

87
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:54,116
And who'd look after the kids?

88
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,920
Me.
No way.

89
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,712
You're too busy.

90
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:02,833
It's me who'll take charge
of the children's education.

91
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,519
How sad...

92
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:07,314
...to separate 
from Jean-Charles, so soon.

93
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,078
Yes, I know.

94
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:12,192
But the idea that
he's deceiving me is unbearable.

95
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,834
You've thought about the children?

96
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:16,951
No, I'm thinking about myself.

97
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:21,155
Even among the most united couples,
there are empty times.

98
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,191
And then... they go away!

99
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:26,790
Or don't go away.
You know about that.

100
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,309
How long 've you been
sleeping apart from Papa?

101
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,715
I don't want to
talk about that.

102
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:35,549
When did he last behave like a husband
with you?

103
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:38,638
D'you think
I'd go into that!

104
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,359
There's more to life than sex,
little girl.

105
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,238
At your age, perhaps.

106
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:46,075
Your father works so hard!
In the evening he's tired.

107
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,548
Maybe he's deceiving you.

108
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,916
I forbid you
to criticize your father.

109
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,559
I'm not criticizing him,

110
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,268
It's you.
You've just accepted everything... everything!

111
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,995
You pretend not to see,
but he does just as he wants.

112
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,549
I've always been impervious
to gossip.

113
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:04,992
And then I have my grandchildren,
my garden, my poems ...

114
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:07,590
But are you happy, Mama?

115
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,551
Of course I'm happy.

116
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,950
I decided that...
once and for all.

117
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:15,799
But me, I don't want
this pathetic life.

118
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,390
I'd rather divorce.

119
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:22,950
How are you going to live, 
if you divorce.

120
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,913
I'll ask Papa for
a position at the factory.

121
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,752
That's not a bad idea.

122
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,791
You need to know it's what you want.

123
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:31,917
Me... at least, I know.

124
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:38,151
The worst thing for me would be
to become like you: "une potiche"... a trophy wife.

125
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:41,715
Joel!!!

126
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:44,155
You do it on purpose, don't you?

127
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,920
Don't park outside the entrance!

128
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,680
I stopped by for
Mama's birthday.

129
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:52,075
Who's birth...
Forgot?

130
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:54,072
That bitch Nadège forgot.

131
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:58,512
She's got other things to think about think.
Buy whatever you want

132
00:10:58,760 --> 00:10:59,875
I'll pay you back.

133
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:02,310
Papa, you never change.

134
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:05,193
Tonight try to
be in a better mood.

135
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,038
I need to talk to you.

136
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:13,190
You know what she wants?
Divorce.

137
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:16,073
She's trading in Jean-Charles for someone else?
No!

138
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,271
She wants to work with her beloved father 
at the factory.

139
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,675
No-way-in-the-world-and-the-kids-good...

140
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,791
Gotta get my drops.

141
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:25,998
Laurent's not here?
He'll be here tonight.

142
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,236
He's got good news for us.

143
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,874
I'm wary of good news...
...especially concerning your son.

144
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,878
I think he wants to get married.
Great...eh?

145
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,877
Supporting a new family ...

146
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,674
But he's not asking you for anything.
That'll come.

147
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:42,555
The girl who's got her hooks into him
knows what she's at.

148
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,830
I reassure you,
her family is respectable.

149
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:47,713
She's the daughter of the Cathedral Square baker,


150
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:50,190
Floriane Marquiset.
Robert!

151
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,470
My God! But ...

152
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,477
Name of God, dammit!

153
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:57,990
It seems she's nice.
She's studied piano.

154
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,599
She studied the piano?

155
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,910
Would you've preferred the clarinet?

156
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:05,675
It's beyond belief for him
to marry Floriane Marquiset.

157
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:09,236
A Pujol with a Marquiset,
..... it'd be a disgrace.

158
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:13,069
You're being way too snobbish.
Wait 'til you meet her.

159
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,952
I'll never meet her.

160
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:17,549
And Laurent will not marry
Marquiset's daughter!

161
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:20,194
You understand?
If you want my opinion ...

162
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:22,311
Your "opinion"?
You have an opinion?

163
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:28,319
All I ask of you
is to share mine.

164
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:32,235
Be nice,
Just keep to your little poems.

165
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:36,717
Joel is right.
I'm just a trophy wife.

166
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:39,480
I lay there in a corner ...

167
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,398
I'm just part of the decor.

168
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:45,229
Are you challenging me too?

169
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:48,477
Name me one woman as indulged as you are.

170
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:51,797
With regard to household appliances,
I'm queen.

171
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,560
You have everything,
you have to agree.

172
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:57,877
Now the phone.
What a life!

173
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,599
Hello?

174
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,238
Oh ...can't be true!

175
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,953
Dammit!

176
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,673
Oh, damn!

177
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:09,558
I'm coming.
What's still going? I'm coming.

178
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:12,593
It never stops.
They're striking at workshop 4.

179
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,949
A strike?

180
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,835
It'll cost me millions.

181
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:20,679
What'll you do?
What'll I do...fight!

182
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:23,036
The ... But Robert ...

183
00:13:23,640 --> 00:13:27,428
Be careful though. 
I'll go mad...

184
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,518
A strike!

185
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,438
A strike ...

186
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,668
"The rose in the morning

187
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,154
"Opens at noon

188
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:01,390
"Ephemeral destiny

189
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:07,469
"Died at midnight."

190
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:25,029
How's Papa?

191
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:28,158
Always in a bad mood
with these strikes.

192
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:31,193
You think it'll get better tonight?
Hopefully.

193
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:34,676
I'm sure he'll be charming...
being my birthday.

194
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:39,397
Are you happy the way your studies are going?
I've had a gut-full.

195
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,034
Political Science just isn't my thing.

196
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:44,913
What is your thing?
I dunno, Mama.

197
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,997
Are you still taking drawing courses?

198
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,395
No time...
... and what's the point?

199
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,238
What a shame, you were gifted.

200
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:53,795
I wish we had
an artist in the family.

201
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,395
You know what would make me happy?
What?

202
00:14:56,600 --> 00:15:00,639
Come to work at the plant.
Not interested in the plant.

203
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,512
I wouldn't ever want
to work with Papa.

204
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:06,269
To end with the boss syndrome...
hated by everyone ...

205
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,994
Your grandfather
was adored by everyone.

206
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,636
Mama, paternalism,
It's over, old-fashioned.

207
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:15,195
Today's man must be a bastard,

208
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,914
orders, unbridled capitalism.

209
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:21,954
Tell me, when did
you meet this Floriane?

210
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,593
It's been six months.

211
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,836
We met on the train
when I came at Christmas.

212
00:15:26,040 --> 00:15:27,473
That's romantic.

213
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:30,274
You're sure you're in love?
Yes, Mama.

214
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:32,630
She's crazy about me.

215
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:35,513
So much the better.
That makes for happiness.

216
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:40,475
One Sunday, after Mass
we stopped by her mother's bakery

217
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:42,796
and got a house special... a Bombe Glacée.

218
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:47,077
I recognised the beautiful Madame Marquiset
behind her counter,

219
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,748
always so well dressed.

220
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,393
She died
electrocuted by a hairdryer.

221
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,591
You thinking about getting married?

222
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,074
That's what she wants.

223
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,912
When'll we meet her?

224
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:02,958
Once she's finished
her exams in Paris.

225
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,718
How nice!

226
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:07,918
Grandma, look what I did
for your birthday.

227
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:10,509
Fabián, you were supposed 
to to wait for dessert.

228
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:13,274
- Let him.
It's so nice.

229
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,192
Thank you, Fabián.

230
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,914
When's Papa coming?
I dunno.

231
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,429
His schedule
is very mysterious.

232
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:23,871
What is it, exactly?
Terrorists

233
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,588
with machine guns.
It's fun.

234
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,074
What imagination!

235
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:31,392
Grandma, I'll do
an imitation of Coluche.

236
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:35,229
No, Stanislaus,
not that horrible Coluche here.

237
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:37,710
Yet it's funny.  No, it's vulgar

238
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,279
Paris would like it.

239
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:43,354
It'd do you good to travel.
Your Jean-Charles never takes you anywhere?

240
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,591
Please Laurent, not now.

241
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:48,559
That's Papa. I'll get the door.
He's got his key.

242
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:52,110
I'm coming, Papa. I'm coming.

243
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:58,073
Nadège? What're you doing here?
I must see Madame Pujol. It's very urgent.

244
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:00,236
She's is in the lounge.

245
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,988
Mademoiselle Nadège?
Madame, it's terrible.

246
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,236
Terrible?...
... Papa?

247
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:10,910
Yes. Monsieur Pujol ...
He had an attack?

248
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:12,712
No. He's locked in.

249
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,592
Locked in?
Yes.

250
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,711
He fought
with the foreman.

251
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:19,514
The workers have locked him
in his office.

252
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:22,917
I was sure there was something...
he was so on edge this morning!

253
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,957
Do they have
machine guns?

254
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:28,431
Stanislaus, Flavian
go upstairs.

255
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,951
You must call the commissioner,
to send a mediator.

256
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:34,434
We must get the riot squad.

257
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:38,832
We won't get anywhere with tear gas.

258
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:43,079
These workers have got outside the law.
We must act with diplomacy.

259
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:44,952
Obviously.
You side with the left.

260
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:47,720
Beside you,
everyone is left.

261
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:49,990
That's enough, calm down.
Mademoiselle,

262
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:52,151
what do they want
exactly?

263
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:55,352
They require new
health care.

264
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,591
This is not too much to ask.

265
00:17:57,840 --> 00:18:01,958
The toilets are long-standing grievance.
They're Turkish-style!

266
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,838
It's all a political pretext.

267
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:07,396
They demand everything now:
Increase in staff...

268
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:10,154
a Christmas bonus ...

269
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,239
Remove surveillance.

270
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,550
Obviously, that's a lot.

271
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,392
It's that filthy Babin
who's behind it.

272
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,519
He stirs up revolt.

273
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,676
You heard him
on the radio?

274
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,792
That man makes my flesh crawl.

275
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,912
He'll be OK if he takes his drops.
He always forgets.

276
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:31,715
If I wasn't there ...
...rather... if you weren't there ...

277
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:35,071
....if we weren't there.
Don't apologize.

278
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:38,118
Well I'll go ...

279
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,794
Where are you going?

280
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,679
I'm his son.
They can take me hostage in his place.

281
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:46,229
Anyway.
I appreciate this.

282
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:48,714
I'm off.

283
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,555
Come on.

284
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:05,357
They're letting him go?
They talked with him.

285
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:08,398
It's Hubert
One of the worst.

286
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,670
I hope they'll
come to an agreement.

287
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:12,836
More and more are coming.

288
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,632
They're waving banners.

289
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:17,559
They wrote
on the wall:

290
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:20,593
"Pujol equals...oh!... Hitler."

291
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,269
They're exaggerating.

292
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:26,233
Besides the little bit
on the face ...

293
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:29,351
They're getting more worked up.

294
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:30,788
I'm scared.
Me too.

295
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,878
Nadège, lock the door.

296
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,912
Madame! Madame!

297
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:46,918
They're approaching the house.
Calm down.

298
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:50,715
Marie Antoinette found herself
in the same situation.

299
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:53,912
She still finished
under the guillotine.

300
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:55,951
What are they shouting?

301
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:57,912
Pujol ... Fed up ...

302
00:19:58,120 --> 00:19:59,439
Pujol, fed ...

303
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,790
PUJOL, fed up!

304
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,831
PUJOL, fed up!

305
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:07,032
PUJOL, fed up!
PUJOL, fed up!

306
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,316
What are you doing here?

307
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:11,033
A moment of relaxation.

308
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:14,391
Some of the claims
aren't that unjustified.

309
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:18,149
Model secretary
turns into rabid unionist.

310
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,396
It won't last long.

311
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:23,359
I'm not turning into anything, 
but salaried staff've gotta to take a stand.

312
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:26,956
You don't know what's what,
you're the boss's daughter.

313
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,475
It's better than the boss's chick.
I forbid you ...

314
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:33,112
Who is it?
I'll go.

315
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:36,437
If it's the workers, don't open.
Trust me.

316
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:39,069
Who's there?

317
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:41,236
Laurent? Already?

318
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:43,152
You're not hurt, at least.

319
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,833
Assaulting my brother!

320
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:47,156
They're madmen.
No, you weren't there.

321
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:49,715
It wasn't the workers. papa.
Papa?

322
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,239
Robert?

323
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:54,910
The workers helped me
to see Papa.

324
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:59,432
I tried to reason with
him to make concessions.

325
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:03,235
He jumped on me screaming 
that I was a moron.

326
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:07,111
Luckily, the picket line
hemmed him in.

327
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:09,914
In this case,
it's better I go.

328
00:21:10,120 --> 00:21:12,076
Mama,
they'll laugh at you.

329
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:15,556
I don't want your father's death 
on my conscience.

330
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:18,911
You want me with you?
No, darling.

331
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:21,076
It's better I go alone.

332
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:51,956
It's the boss's wife!

333
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:19,150
Yes?
Monsieur Deputy-Mayor, good evening.

334
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,279
Madame Pujol?

335
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,829
Can I come in?
Yes, of course.

336
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,712
Yes ...

337
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:42,714
I'm sorry
to receive you like this.

338
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,753
I'm not here
for a society event.

339
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,757
Good...then sit down.

340
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:51,192
To my left or my right.
Wherever you want.

341
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:58,676
What can I do for you,
Madame Pujol?

342
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:01,997
Monsieur Deputy-Mayor,
I came to ask you

343
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:05,550
to use your influence
to release my husband.

344
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:09,679
A dialogue needs to be opened 
with the union delegates.

345
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:14,630
My husband refuses.

346
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:18,230
I think it would be much better
to negotiate in a friendly manner.

347
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:22,189
"Friendly manner"?
One worker was attacked!

348
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:24,078
My husband is impulsive.

349
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:25,639
His left fist
alone?

350
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:29,190
Why are you being so aggressive?

351
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:32,034
I don't see why
I should help you.

352
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:36,990
You didn't always say that,
if you know what I mean.

353
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:40,550
Don't bring up the past.

354
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:45,157
Would our moment of madness be
incompatible with your image?

355
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:48,710
Or, for that matter, with the image
a perfect wife.

356
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:51,510
Without you, perhaps I would be.

357
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:54,320
Don't try to blame me.

358
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,278
After all,

359
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:58,670
youthful indiscretions
do happen.

360
00:24:58,920 --> 00:24:59,796
You stinker!

361
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,992
It was the same for you
as for me.

362
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:06,869
You were a girl, boss's wife
and I was a worker.

363
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:09,793
I betrayed my class.  And I my husband.

364
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:11,393
Which is worse?

365
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:17,149
I remember
I was returning from a wedding.

366
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:18,509
Monsieur! Monsieur!

367
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:21,314
I'd punctured a tire on the road.

368
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:24,438
By chance we crossed paths.

369
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:28,519
- It was my usual route.
I'll help a neighbour

370
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:32,912
even if I disagree
with their politics.

371
00:25:33,120 --> 00:25:33,996
Hello.

372
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:36,959
You should have seen
the state of your dress.

373
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:37,910
Hello.

374
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:40,037
All stained with grease,

375
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:43,317
the jack in hand.

376
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:47,473
I wore a dress in organza
with a pink cape.

377
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:51,468
I changed your wheel
and you made me smile,

378
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:55,150
abandoning for a moment
the arrogance of your caste.

379
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:57,868
Grandpa was a boilermaker.

380
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:01,078
You refused the tip I offered.

381
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:03,714
But I accepted a cigarette.

382
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:08,317
We went to have a smoke together,
in the shade of a walnut tree.

383
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:11,273
As we went
into the brush.

384
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:14,677
You must have thought
me an easy woman.

385
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,677
No, Suzanne.

386
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:26,634
The very next day
you resumed your distance

387
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:30,355
and firmly drew
the curtain on our adventure.

388
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:32,630
I was married, a mother.

389
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:34,910
I had a social status to maintain.

390
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:39,318
So many times I feared
you'd brag about it.

391
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:44,230
I can hold my tongue when the honor
of a woman is at stake.

392
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,476
Thank you.
Good.

393
00:26:46,720 --> 00:26:49,359
You want your husband back?

394
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:51,755
Yes.
But if I get his release

395
00:26:51,960 --> 00:26:54,315
I'll need a return match.

396
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:56,112
A return match?

397
00:26:56,320 --> 00:27:00,029
Sir, I daren't understand....
....at our age?

398
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:01,958
No, you misunderstand.

399
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:05,357
It's no longer a horny truck-driver
facing you.

400
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:08,597
I'm confused. Forgive me.
No, forget it...

401
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:11,314
In other circumstances ...
Oh yes?

402
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,839
Let's get off the subject.

403
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:17,511
I'm thinking about the role you might
play within the factory.

404
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:18,630
Meaning...?

405
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:22,276
If reforms are not
applied in the immediate future,

406
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:25,313
the company will be closed


407
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,875
and 300 workers unemployed.

408
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:30,469
That's a lot.
Yes, Suzanne.

409
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:55,278
So? What did the doctor say?
I don't know.

410
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:56,993
He's still with Papa.

411
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:59,316
Does he know how
he was released?

412
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:01,875
Better not tell him.

413
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:04,674
How humiliating for him!
Freed by his worst enemy.

414
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:08,509
If the riot squad had been on the job,
we wouldn't have needed him

415
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:10,073
Don't be simple.

416
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:13,989
Even the communists have a heart.
That's what destroys a man.

417
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:16,800
His gaze wasn't the same.

418
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,439
Don't worry, he'll recover OK.

419
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:21,240
And if I made him
my special broth?

420
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:23,276
Why not.

421
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:36,674
You need rest, darling.       
But it's not that serious.

422
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:39,718
You're not
safe from another attack,

423
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:42,115
and you may have
a pulmonary endema.

424
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:46,438
You must spend one week
in hospital for tests.

425
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:50,269
But the factory?
The factory...the factory... it'll fold without you?

426
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,994
I'll leave you.
Here's the prescription.

427
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:57,159
Monsieur Pujol, I expect you
at the hospital this week.

428
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:58,429
That's it!

429
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:00,153
Thank you, doctor.
See you soon.

430
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:04,432
Have you talked to Laurent
about the Marquiset girl?

431
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:08,195
Did you tell him to forget her?

432
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:10,635
You don't understand...he's in love.

433
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:13,195
You're forcing me to reveal
something unpleasant

434
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:18,316
You give me no choice.

435
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:22,559
I have reason to believe
Floriane is partly my daughter.

436
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,438
What do you mean
"partly your daughter"?

437
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:29,310
Her mother told me.
Her mother's no longer of this world ...

438
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:32,438
So Madame Marquiset
was your mistress?

439
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,477
Straightaway... out come the big words!

440
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:36,073
What a fine husband!

441
00:29:36,320 --> 00:29:38,197
Your reaction's a little late.

442
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:40,510
How was I supposed to know?

443
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:42,910
It's true that we were....
....discrete.

444
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:44,798
She was married.

445
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,753
She wasn't arousing
her husband's suspicions.

446
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,319
Exactly.  It's your son's fault.

447
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:51,278
Of all the girls in the world, that mental defective

448
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:54,717
had to go and find Mademoiselle Marquiset.

449
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:59,112
This trumps
the birthday gift that you forgot!

450
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:01,590
You want me to beg your pardon?

451
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:02,989
No. You disgust me.

452
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:08,069
Under these circumstances, you'll agree
that marriage is unthinkable.

453
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:10,959
They're already sleeping together.
Omigod!

454
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:14,749
Your banging the Marquiset woman
won't get you into heaven.

455
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,753
Why, f'Godsake?
It's so long ago.

456
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:20,355
But because ...

457
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:23,870
it's the straw
that broke the trophy wife's back!

458
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,991
Is everything OK, ma'am?
Yes, OK.

459
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,997
I made my special broth.

460
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:38,033
That's nice.
It'll do him good.

461
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:41,510
Cuckoo!

462
00:30:41,760 --> 00:30:43,352
What are you doing here?

463
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:45,830
I'm here

464
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:45,830
I'm here
to give you my little specialty.

465
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,275
Yes.
That can't hurt me.

466
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:53,159
I was talking about 
my special broth.

467
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:58,430
Mademoiselle Nadège is really
a model secretary.

468
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:01,200
She made some broth
for your father.

469
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:04,312
She'll get it in her face.

470
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:07,398
He's here.
Have him come in.

471
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:10,433
Who?
The one who freed your father.

472
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:11,516
That man here?

473
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:13,716
It is you who ...
- That's me.

474
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:16,150
But it's the devil!

475
00:31:18,280 --> 00:31:19,508
Hello.

476
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:22,712
Welcome, Monsieur Deputy.
And thank you again.

477
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:24,592
The union delegates

478
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:26,796
feel they have taken the first step.

479
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:30,316
They require
an immediate response.

480
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:31,509
It's just that my husband

481
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:33,557
isn't well this morning.

482
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:34,556
Tomorrow

483
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:36,677
he may receive visits.

484
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:38,319
You don't give a damn about me?

485
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:39,549
It's the truth...

486
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:42,155
True, he's very weak.

487
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,628
You want a certificate?

488
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:45,871
I've done my part of the bargain.

489
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:47,553
If I plead his case,

490
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:49,392
it's up to the workers to decide.

491
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:51,596
So in the absence of negotiations,

492
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:54,115
I predict a restoration
of the strike.

493
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,679
 As for me, I'll predict

494
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:58,434
my foot up your arse!
Monsieur Pujol!

495
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,159
He doesn't look sick.

496
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:02,072
What are you doing to me?

497
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:05,596
Isn't enough
having humiliated me?

498
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:07,552
Come off it, Papa ...

499
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,432
Shut up, arsehole!

500
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:12,313
Papa, be reasonable.
You'll strain your heart.

501
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:14,795
What have you done to me?

502
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,151
I only promised
Monsieur the Deputy-Mayor that

503
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:21,750
in exchange for your release
you'd consider some requests

504
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,558
...about staff.

505
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:24,835
That I'm for.

506
00:32:25,080 --> 00:32:26,069
Me too.

507
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:28,840
For the brainwashing ...

508
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:32,512
Robert, you do nothing but fight.
You've got to negotiate.

509
00:32:32,720 --> 00:32:33,516
Tell the delegates

510
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:36,115
that if they want
paid holidays,

511
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:38,231
they've got to
return to work.

512
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:41,591
If they want to earn more,
it'll require more work.

513
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:43,711
You thought I was finished, washed up.

514
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,798
My family was ready
to sell off the factory.

515
00:32:47,040 --> 00:32:48,996
Once
the picket lines are removed,

516
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:53,677
I'll show you what 
a boss is who has two of them!

517
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:56,395
- Let me tell you

518
00:32:56,640 --> 00:33:00,519
the Works
has decided to review your accounts.

519
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,830
Whadda you mean?

520
00:33:03,080 --> 00:33:06,834
That your Mercedes is listed
as a company car.

521
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:08,359
Your apartment, your servants,

522
00:33:08,600 --> 00:33:10,556
your home, your boat,

523
00:33:10,800 --> 00:33:12,711
made out to be
company

524
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:15,474
expenses.

525
00:33:15,680 --> 00:33:16,829
Papa!

526
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:20,274
Heart attack, as I predicted.

527
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,590
Raise his head.

528
00:33:22,840 --> 00:33:25,354
Press firmly.

529
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:28,990
My father... a heart-attack.
Send an ambulance.

530
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:31,800
This is where is anger leads to.

531
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:34,679
He'll go to hospital now.

532
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:36,717
What about the factory?

533
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:39,394
Your father should
be replaced

534
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:42,029
by someone with power of attorney.  He transferred it.

535
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:44,510
In this case ...
No. Sorry.

536
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:47,996
The management of a factory,
Not for me.

537
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:49,836
Me?

538
00:33:50,080 --> 00:33:51,559
She's worse than Papa.

539
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:54,439
But then who?
Jean-Charles.

540
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,636
Oh no, not him.

541
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:01,919
Why not you, Madame Pujol?

542
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,875
You're joking?
It'd be above board.

543
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:07,435
The founder's daughter,
the boss's wife.

544
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:08,914
But I don't know anything about it.

545
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:11,031
You won't really be
Plant Manager.

546
00:34:11,240 --> 00:34:13,834
Just sit in
Papa's chair.

547
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:16,031
You won't be given any
responsibilities.

548
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:18,276
Still, I don't know if I ...

549
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:20,948
Suzanne, do what you're told.

550
00:34:21,160 --> 00:34:22,957
Do what you're told.

551
00:34:23,160 --> 00:34:25,196
Better you than someone else.

552
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,709
We've no choice.

553
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:30,388
If it's you who's asking me ...

554
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:34,070
I'ill do nothing to cause you concern.
That's the way.

555
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:37,236
So you agree?

556
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:39,510
In the interest of the factory, yes.

557
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:43,038
It's okay, I'll be fine.

558
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:47,396
I'm trusting on you
to keep me posted.

559
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:49,431
Count on me, boss.

560
00:34:51,640 --> 00:34:53,153
Should I take your place, Madame Pujal?

561
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:55,072
Yes. You do that
very well.

562
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:57,993
No, Nadège.
I'm going with Papa.

563
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,479
It would have been easier

564
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:06,075
if you'd been
successor to your father.

565
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:08,350
You're going with history.

566
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:11,074
Women everywhere
are taking power.

567
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:12,838
Go, go home.

568
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:16,074
You have to speak to Monsieur Babin.

569
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:28,438
In what state of mind
will you meet the committee?

570
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:32,918
Conciliation. Provided
they don't ask for too much.

571
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:34,951
When the workers
demand too much,

572
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:37,720
it's that the boss
doesn't give enough.

573
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:41,229
Good. We must prepare
a little script,

574
00:35:41,440 --> 00:35:45,149
so what you
say'll be without stuttering.

575
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:46,839
That's a good idea.

576
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:49,719
Me, I'd start with:

577
00:35:49,920 --> 00:35:54,311
"Gentlemen, I come to you
in a spirit of understanding ... "

578
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:57,120
"Gentlemen"?
It's cold, it's snobbish.

579
00:35:57,320 --> 00:36:00,551
I 'd say "my friends".
I wouldn't recommend that.

580
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:02,352
These aren't your friends.

581
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:03,953
Maybe they'll become so.

582
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:06,839
That'd take action,
not empty words.

583
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:09,753
Good. Go on.

584
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:13,037
"In a spirit
of understanding.

585
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,748
"I am just a woman,
but ... "

586
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:20,589
I can't say that.
It's obvious, isn't it?

587
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:23,189
I don't apologize
for being a woman.

588
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:26,358
It's not that ...
You're a misogynist.

589
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:29,597
We support
women's rights.

590
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:32,758
I can't say
"I am a woman."

591
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:36,191
I'll say:
"Yes, I am a woman."

592
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:39,312
Because whether you like it or not,
I'm a woman.

593
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:42,876
But I like it.
I like it very much, Suzanne.

594
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:45,034
They're waiting for you.

595
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:46,190
Already?

596
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:48,630
If we want
work to resume,

597
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:49,875
let's go.

598
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:54,915
How do they seem?
Not very prepossessing.

599
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:57,680
The less they're kept waiting, 
the better it'll be.

600
00:36:57,880 --> 00:37:00,713
I'd like to get myself ready.
You're fine.

601
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:04,708
I know what I am.
They can wait.

602
00:37:06,040 --> 00:37:07,553
No, really.

603
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,470
Does the factory say anything to you?

604
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:17,999
Should it?

605
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:20,634
When you had the luck to be your father's son

606
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:22,478
and when you've done Political Science ...

607
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:25,558
I'm "my father's son?
You are the Pujol son.

608
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:27,711
It doesn't interest me, all that.

609
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:30,115
The money, possessions,
benefits.

610
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,709
I'm against the exploitation of man.


611
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:35,394
Have you told your father that?  
Sort of.

612
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:36,635
What'd he say?

613
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:37,630
I'd be eaten

614
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:39,871
by others.
Typical!

615
00:37:40,080 --> 00:37:41,877
Politically...are you engaged?

616
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:44,680
Politics, protests,
mean very little for me.

617
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:48,111
Everything is political commitment.
Don't wear yourself out.

618
00:37:48,360 --> 00:37:52,831
What interests you?
You really want to know?

619
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:54,390
Yes.

620
00:37:54,640 --> 00:37:58,030
Painting, art history,
Kandinsky ...

621
00:37:58,280 --> 00:37:59,554
Ah yes!

622
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:01,348
Kandinsky, yes.

623
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:03,352
He was a true revolutionary.

624
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:08,034
You see that do you care
about politics.

625
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,196
Che Guevara, Georges Marchais,

626
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:11,759
Kandinsky ...

627
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:15,032
The politics of art.

628
00:38:15,280 --> 00:38:17,953
I enjoy interacting
ideas with youth.

629
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,997
We should have a drink,

630
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:22,071
one day, together.

631
00:38:23,240 --> 00:38:26,471
Yes.

632
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:35,118
What's that?
It's not like you?

633
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:38,630
It's not too much, Mama?
But why?

634
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:42,435
You won't present yourslf to the factory
in this outfit!

635
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:45,438
It's a provocation.
But I wanted to honor the workers.

636
00:38:45,640 --> 00:38:47,358
And I put on all my jewelery.

637
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:50,313
Just for them... they deserve it.

638
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:52,670
Let's hope they enjoy them.

639
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,074
Let's go.

640
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:59,598
It's the dress you ...
Did you recognize it?

641
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:01,631
I hadn't forgotten.

642
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:15,718
The committee's
in the union meeting-room.

643
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:18,115
I've got stage fright.
I'll leave you...

644
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:20,390
...Miss Nadège will accompany you.

645
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:21,999
You're abandoning me?

646
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:26,478
The committee'd take a dim view...
I'm involved in the meeting.

647
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:28,796
Are you sure?
It's OK... go on.

648
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:33,628
Call me when you're done.
It's gonna be alright.

649
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,993
You won't leave me, will you?
No, madame.

650
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:44,433
Is my dress too much?
No, no.

651
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:45,629
That's fine.

652
00:39:45,840 --> 00:39:48,673
Those men will be in for an eyeful.

653
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:49,915
How many are there?

654
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:53,032
Ten, I think.
Hope they're nice.

655
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,314
Gentlemen.

656
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:02,151
Good morning, gentlemen.
Hello Madame Pujol.

657
00:40:02,360 --> 00:40:04,112
Sit down, guys.

658
00:40:14,680 --> 00:40:15,556
My dear friends,

659
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:18,917
as you know,
my husband was hospitalized.

660
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,838
I'm standing in for him

661
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:23,355
until the end of his convalescence.

662
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:25,670
I am delighted to meet you

663
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,911
to get acquainted,

664
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:32,756
so we can chat ...

665
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,991
As you are aware,

666
00:40:35,240 --> 00:40:38,915
your husband is precipitating the factory
into a catastrophic situation.

667
00:40:40,600 --> 00:40:45,276
If we're on strike today,
it's not for fun.

668
00:40:45,520 --> 00:40:47,476
We love our work.

669
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:49,033
We're fed up

670
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:51,840
I can here you quite well, André ...

671
00:40:52,040 --> 00:40:53,109
No need

672
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:55,749
to get so angry.
Moreover,

673
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,389
I'm pleased to see
the progress you've made.

674
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:01,635
My father who took you on
as an apprentice

675
00:41:01,880 --> 00:41:04,440
'd be proud to know you're
still here.

676
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:07,797
So what are
your concerns, my friend?

677
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:10,918
Madame Pujol
I'll be very clear.

678
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:13,111
We will not resume work

679
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:16,517
until the following claims
have been implemented.

680
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:19,280
1. Award of the Christmas bonus
to all employees

681
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:22,910
effective retroactively
January 1.

682
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:25,549
2. The fifth week
of paid leave.

683
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:29,956
3. Reorganization
of working time

684
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:32,430
and standardization of 40 hours

685
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:36,110
with extra hours
additional 25%

686
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:40,911
pursuant to Article 1 ...

687
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:42,473
As Papa said:

688
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:44,153
"There is no need

689
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:46,868
"To load the mule
for it to reach its destination. "

690
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:50,112
In any case,
I agree with you.

691
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:51,918
Things aren't good here any more.

692
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:57,148
It's time we once again had
the desire to work in fraternity and solidarity.

693
00:41:58,240 --> 00:42:00,071
Concretely, what does that mean?

694
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:03,232
I swear on the heads
my children and my father

695
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:05,158
to examine your demands

696
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,470
with the most sincere attention

697
00:42:07,720 --> 00:42:08,994
to improve

698
00:42:09,240 --> 00:42:10,992
the situation in our factory.

699
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,798
As you know,
I am the wife

700
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:13,995
of Monsieur Pujol.

701
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:17,516
So he's my boss too.
So I can understand you.

702
00:42:17,760 --> 00:42:20,957
Except that I'm
not about to strike.

703
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:23,193
Congratulations, boss.

704
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:30,151
- Mama? Mama?

705
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:32,070
So?

706
00:42:32,280 --> 00:42:35,113
How did it go?

707
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:38,598
They go back to work tomorrow.
That's great!

708
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:41,678
I knew you could do it.
So you've given in on everything?

709
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:44,110
No. We negotiated.

710
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:47,437
You know, I really thought
about the situation.

711
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:50,757
I want to ask a sacrifice of you both.

712
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:53,230
I want you to be
at my side.

713
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:56,074
We are
at your side, Mama.

714
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:58,191
To work with me.

715
00:42:58,440 --> 00:43:00,271
Joel, I want to propose

716
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:02,556
you help me with the management.

717
00:43:04,520 --> 00:43:05,999
At the factory, with you?

718
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:09,835
I know you want to work with 
your father. I'm making the proposal.

719
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:12,110
Thank you, Mama!

720
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:14,151
You gonna mess my hair!
And I'm going out tonight.

721
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:17,796
I'm sure it will make things better between 
you and Jean-Charles.

722
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:21,350
And I'll do what?
I've got my Political Science classes. 

723
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:24,637
The experience 'd be good for you.


724
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:26,438
It doesn't interest me.

725
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:29,148
We'll find you an
artistic position.

726
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:33,518
And Floriane in Paris? I can't leave her.
I'd forgotten about that.

727
00:43:33,720 --> 00:43:37,269
On weekends, we'll
have concerts at the factory.

728
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:41,758
Music doesn't do any harm,
especially to the workers.

729
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:43,558
So... to us!

730
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:45,711
To the Pujol-Michonneau factory.

731
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:48,713
To the Pujol-Michonneau factory!

732
00:43:48,920 --> 00:43:52,680
[Baccara: "Do you speak French?"]

733
00:44:10,080 --> 00:44:12,958
Who's the bourgeois bimbo
with the yokel?

734
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:15,833
Hey! Isn't it
that woman at Pujol's ...right?

735
00:44:16,040 --> 00:44:18,554
Pujol? Our Pujol?

736
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:20,999
What are you smiling at?

737
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:25,113
Imagine Robert's face
if he saw me here, and with you.

738
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:27,592
The poor man.

739
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:29,870
Thank you for your help
at the factory.

740
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:32,753
I couldn't have done it alone.
It was nothing.

741
00:44:32,960 --> 00:44:35,713
You know what surprises me the most?
No.

742
00:44:35,920 --> 00:44:39,993
Is to celebrate the end of the strike,
here with you, at the 'Bada-Boom'.

743
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:42,760
I know this isn't
my sort of place,

744
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:44,712
but I've dreamt
of coming.

745
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:47,070
He brings his clients here.

746
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:50,033
Tonight, Suzanne
I'm the one who's your client.

747
00:44:51,240 --> 00:44:55,438
[Once Upon a Time: "Come take a walk in the rain."]

748
00:46:28,360 --> 00:46:29,759
Thank you.

749
00:46:31,840 --> 00:46:33,239
Forgiveness.

750
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:36,872
Couldn't we start again from scratch?

751
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:38,559
Alas ...

752
00:46:38,760 --> 00:46:41,354
You're the woman of my life
Suzanne.

753
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:44,313
And if we had
our life together?

754
00:46:44,520 --> 00:46:46,351
It's impossible.

755
00:46:46,560 --> 00:46:48,676
You're forgetting about your mistress.

756
00:46:48,880 --> 00:46:51,599
Who told you about that?
That was a dirty trick.

757
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:55,839
It is called 'politics'... a demanding rival.

758
00:46:56,040 --> 00:46:57,837
You know, Suzanne,

759
00:46:58,040 --> 00:47:01,237
the old activist in me
begins to falter.

760
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:03,908
This revolution
I've fought for...

761
00:47:04,120 --> 00:47:06,634
...I sometimes wonder
if I'll ever see it.

762
00:47:06,840 --> 00:47:09,957
I'm still fighting
so generations to come

763
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:12,310
'll know a better world.

764
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:14,397
But I've a right to happiness, 
haven't I?.

765
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:16,033
Would you get it from me?

766
00:47:16,240 --> 00:47:19,152
I've got a heavy name to wear:
Michonneau-Pujol.

767
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:21,550
But you'll change.

768
00:47:21,800 --> 00:47:23,711
How will you introduce me?

769
00:47:23,920 --> 00:47:26,992
Comrade Suzanne?
I can already hear the jeers.

770
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:29,037
I'll explain to them.

771
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:31,635
That you also love justice.

772
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:33,836
You'll share our beliefs.

773
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:36,998
We'll see a brighter future... together.
.

