 Women's work,
you are for it?

1019
01:00:32,240 --> 01:00:35,198
 It gives an impression
of equality with men.

1020
01:00:35,440 --> 01:00:37,317
 The husband should earn
enough money

1021
01:00:37,560 --> 01:00:39,869
 so his wife
could stay at home.

1022
01:00:40,120 --> 01:00:41,553
 It's our job.

1023
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:44,872
 This is not a bad idea.
It brings money.

1024
01:00:45,120 --> 01:00:48,908
 She may not have
a salary like yours?

1025
01:00:49,160 --> 01:00:52,357
 It should fullfill them.
If they stay at home

1026
01:00:52,560 --> 01:00:53,754
 After this break.

1027
01:00:57,480 --> 01:00:58,959
Oh, Joel!

1028
01:00:59,160 --> 01:01:02,436
My darling!
I'm glad to see you.

1029
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:05,355
My! you're beautiful.

1030
01:01:05,920 --> 01:01:08,309
It seems
you work at the plant.

1031
01:01:08,520 --> 01:01:10,750
Mama trusts me.

1032
01:01:10,960 --> 01:01:13,713
More reproaches!
You're all against me?

1033
01:01:13,920 --> 01:01:15,512
But no.
We missed you.

1034
01:01:15,720 --> 01:01:18,757
I'm flattened, Joel.
Your mother's finished me off.

1035
01:01:18,960 --> 01:01:21,474
I know
She's become another woman.

1036
01:01:21,680 --> 01:01:26,310
With her it's all about
"Participation" and "Self-Management."

1037
01:01:26,520 --> 01:01:30,593
Jean-Charles is very concerned
about the future of the factory.

1038
01:01:30,800 --> 01:01:34,839
But she got things through
that Babin refused you.

1039
01:01:35,080 --> 01:01:37,640
Yes... that's it, it's Babin.
She's his toy.

1040
01:01:37,880 --> 01:01:40,269
He manipulates.

1041
01:01:40,520 --> 01:01:41,555
He's humping her?

1042
01:01:41,800 --> 01:01:44,314
Oh, Daddy!
I'd rather not know.

1043
01:01:44,560 --> 01:01:47,074
In my opinion, it's a not new situation

1044
01:01:47,320 --> 01:01:48,833
I found this.

1045
01:01:57,080 --> 01:01:58,911
The bitch!

1046
01:01:59,120 --> 01:02:01,998
So it was him.
"Him" What?

1047
01:02:02,200 --> 01:02:04,350
She'll pay for this.

1048
01:02:14,280 --> 01:02:16,953
Hello. I want to talk
Monsieur Babin.

1049
01:02:17,160 --> 01:02:20,038
You have an appointment?
I'm Monsieur Pujol.

1050
01:02:20,240 --> 01:02:21,878
Robert Pujol.

1051
01:02:22,120 --> 01:02:24,953
Monsieur Babin, hello.
Monsieur Pujol is back.

1052
01:02:25,200 --> 01:02:27,873
Back, yes.
And I need your help.

1053
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:31,277
I have a report on measures
planned by my wife.

1054
01:02:31,520 --> 01:02:34,193
To undo anything
you did.

1055
01:02:34,400 --> 01:02:35,913
What have I done?

1056
01:02:36,160 --> 01:02:38,310
The wildcat strike,
my confinement,

1057
01:02:38,520 --> 01:02:41,956
all that has been conducted
masterfully.

1058
01:02:42,200 --> 01:02:45,476
Then you arrange
to make the report public about

1059
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:48,712
who wants to reduce
staff and relocate.

1060
01:02:48,920 --> 01:02:52,469
I will not tell you
your job, Babin.

1061
01:02:52,680 --> 01:02:54,033
And I want my job.

1062
01:02:54,280 --> 01:02:57,397
Better you convince your board.

1063
01:02:57,600 --> 01:02:59,556
Especially your workers.

1064
01:02:59,800 --> 01:03:02,314
You are a mass manipulator
Babin.

1065
01:03:02,520 --> 01:03:04,511
And with
money to put on the table ...

1066
01:03:04,760 --> 01:03:08,435
D'you take me for a clown
who favors employers?

1067
01:03:08,680 --> 01:03:11,319
You're a two-faced man
my dear.

1068
01:03:13,920 --> 01:03:17,595
What do you imply?
What were you doing with my wife

1069
01:03:17,800 --> 01:03:20,234
at the Bada-Boom?
What?

1070
01:03:20,480 --> 01:03:23,870
Don't make out innocent.
And expect more.

1071
01:03:24,080 --> 01:03:27,709
You were seen with Madame Pujol
in the cafeteria of the Sofitel.

1072
01:03:27,960 --> 01:03:32,238
We met to talk about
working conditions at the factory.

1073
01:03:32,480 --> 01:03:36,029
With all those precautions
to not be recognized?

1074
01:03:36,280 --> 01:03:38,350
We wanted to avoid
talk.

1075
01:03:38,600 --> 01:03:41,672
What would
your constituents

1076
01:03:41,880 --> 01:03:43,598
and the Central Committee do

1077
01:03:43,800 --> 01:03:47,952
if they found
in the local rag

1078
01:03:48,160 --> 01:03:51,550
a photo of
incorruptible member

1079
01:03:51,760 --> 01:03:55,150
trying to break out the champagne
with Madame Pujol.

1080
01:03:55,360 --> 01:03:57,430
Why create a scandal that

1081
01:03:57,640 --> 01:03:59,949
will explode in everyone's face??

1082
01:04:00,160 --> 01:04:02,993
Why?
Because I am a man betrayed

1083
01:04:03,200 --> 01:04:05,760
and I don't care about the scandal.
Listen,

1084
01:04:05,960 --> 01:04:08,872
Nothing has happened
between your wife and me.

1085
01:04:09,080 --> 01:04:11,548
And 25 years ago?

1086
01:04:16,840 --> 01:04:18,319
- My God!

1087
01:04:19,520 --> 01:04:21,033
That's me.

1088
01:04:21,800 --> 01:04:24,189
Suzanne loves me, then.

1089
01:04:25,560 --> 01:04:27,471
It may cost you

1090
01:04:27,680 --> 01:04:31,912
if I reveal that your adventure
produced a brat,

1091
01:04:32,120 --> 01:04:33,792
my son Laurent.

1092
01:04:34,000 --> 01:04:35,513
Laurent?

1093
01:04:36,880 --> 01:04:38,711
Your son?

1094
01:04:39,360 --> 01:04:41,920
My son?
Alas, yes.

1095
01:04:42,120 --> 01:04:44,918
You sure?
Oh, I wasn't there, was I?

1096
01:04:45,920 --> 01:04:48,229
Life is strange.

1097
01:04:48,440 --> 01:04:50,749
We believe ourselves a hardened old fighter...


1098
01:04:50,960 --> 01:04:53,554
and find we're a young papa.

1099
01:04:53,760 --> 01:04:59,562
Your blackmailing has made
me the happiest of men.

1100
01:04:58,920 --> 01:05:02,708
Anyway, if you
don't organise this strike for me,

1101
01:05:02,920 --> 01:05:07,436
Your career is shattered.
Yes. Yes, Pujol.

1102
01:05:07,680 --> 01:05:10,797
Our main
competitors, the Chinese.

1103
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:14,151
are very interested ...
Madame Pujol?

1104
01:05:14,400 --> 01:05:16,755
My mother's doing an interview.

1105
01:05:16,960 --> 01:05:19,679
It makes me happy to see you.
Me too.

1106
01:05:19,920 --> 01:05:24,232
What youth, what enthusiasm!
Are you alright, Mr. Babin?

1107
01:05:25,040 --> 01:05:28,476
That hair, that smile,
the look ...

1108
01:05:28,680 --> 01:05:29,715
Monsieur Deputy-Mayor?

1109
01:05:29,960 --> 01:05:33,316
Would you tell them
how the region is proud

1110
01:05:33,560 --> 01:05:35,039
to have a woman like me ...

1111
01:05:35,240 --> 01:05:37,708
I won't be part of
your personality

1112
01:05:37,960 --> 01:05:39,552
worship.

1113
01:05:39,760 --> 01:05:41,876
Excuse him, he's a communist.

1114
01:05:42,120 --> 01:05:44,793
It makes me happy
see you, you.

1115
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:45,830
Me too ...

1116
01:05:46,080 --> 01:05:47,274
I'm all yours.

1117
01:05:48,880 --> 01:05:51,394
Could we see
her alone?

1118
01:05:51,600 --> 01:05:53,431
Let's go to my office.

1119
01:05:53,640 --> 01:05:56,757
I'd rather do it in my car.
In your car?

1120
01:05:56,960 --> 01:05:58,029
It's uncomfortable.

1121
01:05:58,280 --> 01:06:00,748
Follow me.

1122
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:03,195
You'll look after these gentlemen?
Yes.

1123
01:06:03,400 --> 01:06:05,868
Be careful.
Babin's a bit weird.

1124
01:06:06,120 --> 01:06:07,792
Yes, I'm coming, coming.

1125
01:06:57,320 --> 01:07:00,198
Your husband came to see me.

1126
01:07:00,400 --> 01:07:04,234
Is it true, Suzanne
that your son is mine?

1127
01:07:04,440 --> 01:07:07,557
That my son
is not his.

1128
01:07:07,760 --> 01:07:10,069
Is this gossip
behind my back....

1129
01:07:10,280 --> 01:07:13,397
What is this nonsense...
The truth.

1130
01:07:13,600 --> 01:07:15,079
Tell me the truth.

1131
01:07:15,280 --> 01:07:19,034
One word can make me
the happiest of men.

1132
01:07:19,240 --> 01:07:21,913
Is Laurent my son?

1133
01:07:22,600 --> 01:07:26,309
I'd wish you that pleasure, 
Monsieur deputy mayor...but...

1134
01:07:26,520 --> 01:07:28,954
If we look
at the dates ...

1135
01:07:29,160 --> 01:07:31,879
my photo
in your locket.

1136
01:07:32,080 --> 01:07:33,832
You've got my medallion?

1137
01:07:34,040 --> 01:07:38,750
I have been looking for months.
Your husband nicked it from you.

1138
01:07:39,520 --> 01:07:41,715
Tell me, ....Laurent?.

1139
01:07:42,520 --> 01:07:44,715
No, Maurice,
It's not you.

1140
01:07:46,920 --> 01:07:48,319
Really?

1141
01:07:48,800 --> 01:07:51,109
So...finally, he's Pujol's.

1142
01:07:51,320 --> 01:07:54,471
No. He's neither yours nor his.

1143
01:07:54,680 --> 01:07:57,114
Whose is he then?

1144
01:07:57,960 --> 01:08:02,829
I've every reason to believe
he's the son of Monsieur Balestra.

1145
01:08:03,040 --> 01:08:04,553
The notary?

1146
01:08:06,280 --> 01:08:09,477
He was a clerk at the time.

1147
01:08:09,680 --> 01:08:12,797
Hard to understand 
when you see him today.

1148
01:08:13,000 --> 01:08:16,310
I was often in his study
discussing Papa's estate.

1149
01:08:17,480 --> 01:08:20,119
He was young, charming.

1150
01:08:20,320 --> 01:08:24,233
In his office there was this big leather sofa.

1151
01:08:24,480 --> 01:08:29,156
Everything suggests that Laurent
is the son of Monsieur Balestra.

1152
01:08:29,360 --> 01:08:33,319
Although, if I were to rely only
on appearances,

1153
01:08:33,520 --> 01:08:35,431
he's the image of Gunnar,

1154
01:08:35,680 --> 01:08:38,638
this cheerful Swede who gave
tennis lessons

1155
01:08:38,880 --> 01:08:41,917
for children,
a tall blond... pretty hefty.

1156
01:08:43,240 --> 01:08:44,719
There've been many?

1157
01:08:44,960 --> 01:08:47,520
No... no others in May '52.

1158
01:08:49,640 --> 01:08:53,349
Poor Pujol married
a bourgeois nymphomaniac.

1159
01:08:53,600 --> 01:08:56,876
You can't judge me
by my youthful indescretions.

1160
01:08:57,080 --> 01:08:58,832
You've benefited.

1161
01:08:59,080 --> 01:09:01,640
I'd put you
on a pedestal.

1162
01:09:01,880 --> 01:09:03,518
I happened to come down.

1163
01:09:03,760 --> 01:09:06,274
I've only had brief adventures.

1164
01:09:06,520 --> 01:09:10,274
That's ancient history.
I've other concerns now.

1165
01:09:10,520 --> 01:09:13,353
Exactly...
what's this here?

1166
01:09:13,600 --> 01:09:17,149
This is the report by Jean-Charles.
I really must read it.

1167
01:09:17,400 --> 01:09:20,597
She'll be angry.
You think I'm going to believe that?

1168
01:09:25,560 --> 01:09:28,757
I'm a man killed twice over,
Suzanne.

1169
01:09:28,960 --> 01:09:32,919
After the revelations of your husband
I thought, as in a dream

1170
01:09:33,120 --> 01:09:34,758
I'd become a father

1171
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:39,198
and your companion. How
could I have fooled myself so much?

1172
01:09:39,440 --> 01:09:41,749
You never stopped
being just the same:

1173
01:09:41,960 --> 01:09:45,714
'Wifey', locked up
in his world of lies.

1174
01:09:47,600 --> 01:09:50,433
And I thought to myself...
a tryst,

1175
01:09:50,640 --> 01:09:52,995
in memory of our meeting!

1176
01:09:53,200 --> 01:09:54,792
Serves me right.

1177
01:09:57,440 --> 01:10:01,228
I beg you kindly
get out of my car.

1178
01:10:01,440 --> 01:10:03,476
The factory's over 5 kilometres

1179
01:10:03,720 --> 01:10:04,948
And I've got high heels.

1180
01:10:05,200 --> 01:10:08,192
This is where our journey ends.

1181
01:10:08,400 --> 01:10:10,516
Farewell, Suzanne. Goodbye.

1182
01:10:50,760 --> 01:10:52,591
Hey!

1183
01:11:23,280 --> 01:11:26,397
Thank you, sir.
You've saved my life.

1184
01:11:28,440 --> 01:11:31,876
How am I going to go?
Oops, my skirt!

1185
01:11:55,480 --> 01:11:57,789
You travel this way often?

1186
01:11:58,000 --> 01:12:00,389
It happens. Why?

1187
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:04,394
It's pretty, isn't it?

1188
01:12:06,800 --> 01:12:08,438
Very pretty.

1189
01:12:26,200 --> 01:12:29,829
NO TO OUTSOURCING!
NO TO OUTSOURCING!

1190
01:12:30,080 --> 01:12:32,594
 Madame Pujol promised
continual dialogue.

1191
01:12:32,840 --> 01:12:34,239
 It's always the same.

1192
01:12:34,440 --> 01:12:37,955
We trust the bosses,
and then before long... go whistle for it!

1193
01:12:38,200 --> 01:12:40,156
 I condemn the pernicious use


1194
01:12:40,360 --> 01:12:42,874
of this report
which I strongly condemn

1195
01:12:43,080 --> 01:12:44,911
and do not want to use.

1196
01:12:45,160 --> 01:12:47,355
Grandma's beautiful.

1197
01:12:47,600 --> 01:12:49,272
 Many believed in her.

1198
01:12:49,480 --> 01:12:53,439
She continues the politics
of her husband.

1199
01:12:53,680 --> 01:12:57,514
We must return to a report
supported by the unions.

1200
01:12:57,760 --> 01:12:59,990
 I met
the Board of Directors

1201
01:13:00,200 --> 01:13:02,191
to find a solution.

1202
01:13:02,640 --> 01:13:05,200
Hah!
Don't worry, Mama.

1203
01:13:05,400 --> 01:13:07,391
Everyone supports you.

1204
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:10,558
So why the strike?
It's the principle.

1205
01:13:10,760 --> 01:13:13,354
Your father's got
shareholders against me.

1206
01:13:13,560 --> 01:13:16,358
I reassure you,
they'll be on our side.

1207
01:13:16,560 --> 01:13:18,312
Fortunately you're there.

1208
01:13:18,520 --> 01:13:21,353
How'd I have got by
without my son?

1209
01:13:21,560 --> 01:13:24,791
Thank you, Laurent.
This is normal.

1210
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:26,149
Poor Floriane,

1211
01:13:26,360 --> 01:13:29,830
I've kept you from her.
I've learned a lot from you.

1212
01:13:30,040 --> 01:13:32,838
How do I look?
You're perfect, as usual.

1213
01:13:33,040 --> 01:13:34,519
So let's go.

1214
01:13:35,680 --> 01:13:36,829
Hello, my friends.

1215
01:13:37,080 --> 01:13:39,833
Following the incidents
caused by the publication

1216
01:13:40,040 --> 01:13:42,429
of this report, that I've been accused
of commissioning,

1217
01:13:42,680 --> 01:13:46,719
a meeting of this Board
has been called.

1218
01:13:46,960 --> 01:13:50,191
I hope we can discuss this in a fraternal spirit.

1219
01:13:50,440 --> 01:13:54,558
Monsieur Pujol, you wish to speak?

1220
01:13:54,800 --> 01:13:55,915
Yes, Madame Chair.

1221
01:13:56,120 --> 01:13:58,873
I would like
in these circumstances of crisis

1222
01:13:59,120 --> 01:14:01,475
to propose a vote
at the meeting:

1223
01:14:01,720 --> 01:14:04,439
For or against the continuation

1224
01:14:04,680 --> 01:14:06,830
of your plant management,
madame,

1225
01:14:08,640 --> 01:14:11,757
knowing that I am prepared
to take over the reins

1226
01:14:12,000 --> 01:14:13,797
as soon as possible.

1227
01:14:14,040 --> 01:14:15,359
Things are clear.

1228
01:14:15,600 --> 01:14:18,114
The situation calls
for some urgency.

1229
01:14:18,360 --> 01:14:21,193
Good. To a vote then.
Mademoiselle Nadège,

1230
01:14:21,440 --> 01:14:24,477
would you record the votes?
Naturally.

1231
01:14:27,400 --> 01:14:28,958
Starting on my left.

1232
01:14:29,200 --> 01:14:31,077
Do you think I should direct

1233
01:14:31,320 --> 01:14:34,995
the factory management?
Yes, Mama. I'll give my 10%.

1234
01:14:35,240 --> 01:14:36,832
On top of my my 15%

1235
01:14:37,080 --> 01:14:38,399
that's 25%.

1236
01:14:40,600 --> 01:14:41,749
Mademoiselle Genevieve Micheneau?

1237
01:14:41,960 --> 01:14:44,599
I'll keep my confidence in you, Suzanne

1238
01:14:44,840 --> 01:14:47,593
and I give you my 15%.
Thank you, my dear sister.

1239
01:14:47,840 --> 01:14:49,717
Monsieur Pujol?

1240
01:14:49,960 --> 01:14:52,997
I vote against your direction.
It's 45%.

1241
01:14:53,240 --> 01:14:55,151
Okay.

1242
01:14:55,400 --> 01:14:56,719
Gentlemen?

1243
01:14:56,960 --> 01:14:59,599
Despite the destabilization
you have suffered,

1244
01:14:59,840 --> 01:15:04,516
we recognize the value
your work in recent months.

1245
01:15:04,760 --> 01:15:06,193
And then,

1246
01:15:06,440 --> 01:15:08,351
we submit our 5%.

1247
01:15:13,440 --> 01:15:17,194
Madame Pujol, 45 per cent.
Monsieur Pujol 45 per cent.

1248
01:15:17,440 --> 01:15:19,112
Leaving only my daughter, Joelle,

1249
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:22,193
whom I have wisely
advised and assisted

1250
01:15:22,440 --> 01:15:24,556
during these last few months.

1251
01:15:28,680 --> 01:15:30,636
I give my 10% ...

1252
01:15:33,760 --> 01:15:35,796
To Robert Pujol, my father.

1253
01:15:37,840 --> 01:15:39,193
Thank you, my daughter.

1254
01:15:39,440 --> 01:15:40,793
The bitch!

1255
01:15:44,080 --> 01:15:45,798
What a bitch!

1256
01:15:54,600 --> 01:15:56,670
Laurent, you have a moment?

1257
01:15:56,920 --> 01:15:59,275
I have very important things to say to you.

1258
01:15:59,480 --> 01:16:01,471
We have nothing to say.
I'm going.

1259
01:16:01,680 --> 01:16:02,669
Listen, Laurent

1260
01:16:02,920 --> 01:16:06,549
I'm getting older and tireder

1261
01:16:06,760 --> 01:16:08,955
and I'm not in great shape.

1262
01:16:09,160 --> 01:16:11,390
I put my energy and passion

1263
01:16:11,600 --> 01:16:13,830
in developing this factory.

1264
01:16:14,080 --> 01:16:17,470
I know that during my absence
You have been remarkable.

1265
01:16:17,720 --> 01:16:22,157
I want you to work here,
to one day take over my estate.

1266
01:16:22,400 --> 01:16:25,073
If you're trying to soften me up.
It's too late.

1267
01:16:25,280 --> 01:16:27,748
It is never too late.

1268
01:16:27,960 --> 01:16:29,757
Especially after
what you just did.

1269
01:16:30,000 --> 01:16:33,515
I've only reclaimed my position 
to make it better for you.

1270
01:16:33,760 --> 01:16:36,228
Your methods disgust me.

1271
01:16:36,440 --> 01:16:39,716
You'll do anything,
even crush your own wife.

1272
01:16:39,960 --> 01:16:42,952
He's warped you!

1273
01:16:43,160 --> 01:16:44,070
That Babin.

1274
01:16:44,320 --> 01:16:46,880
Monsieur Babin has nothing
to do with this.

1275
01:16:47,080 --> 01:16:49,435
Much more than you think.

1276
01:16:49,640 --> 01:16:53,519
So you agree
to remain at the plant

1277
01:16:53,760 --> 01:16:57,958
to work with your father?
My father?

1278
01:16:58,160 --> 01:17:01,038
When you have been
a father for me?

1279
01:17:06,640 --> 01:17:09,029
To think that's it's thanks to me 
that you're here.

1280
01:17:09,240 --> 01:17:12,755
I let you have
a strategic position.

1281
01:17:13,400 --> 01:17:16,472
That is how you thank me.
What ingratitude!

1282
01:17:16,680 --> 01:17:19,194
Papa would've offered me
the same position.

1283
01:17:19,400 --> 01:17:20,958
You're very naive
my daughter.

1284
01:17:21,160 --> 01:17:24,789
If you knew what he said when
I asked him to involve you.

1285
01:17:25,000 --> 01:17:26,194
Don't be cruel.

1286
01:17:26,440 --> 01:17:31,036
But allow me to regret
your lack of female solidarity.

1287
01:17:31,960 --> 01:17:35,032
There is no solidarity,
but of competence.

1288
01:17:35,240 --> 01:17:38,516
You're your father's daughter.
He's happy to use

1289
01:17:38,760 --> 01:17:40,557
Jean-Charles' report.

1290
01:17:40,760 --> 01:17:43,832
I beg you, Mama
don't get angry.

1291
01:17:44,080 --> 01:17:45,832
When you made me out to be a dummy 
who accepted everything!

1292
01:17:46,080 --> 01:17:48,310
But you were happy about it.

1293
01:17:48,560 --> 01:17:53,475
That's what I thought.  What are you going to do?

1294
01:17:53,680 --> 01:17:55,989
What you don't dare to do:
Divorce.

1295
01:17:58,840 --> 01:18:01,115
You can't do that.

1296
01:18:01,360 --> 01:18:04,750
So your mother's to stay
as the servant-trophy-wife?

1297
01:18:04,960 --> 01:18:06,916
I'm entitled to my freedom.

1298
01:18:09,760 --> 01:18:10,909
But why ...

1299
01:18:13,320 --> 01:18:16,949
Why should I fight you
when I'm your mother?

1300
01:18:18,840 --> 01:18:21,673
You want the truth, Mama?
Sure.

1301
01:18:22,360 --> 01:18:24,749
I voted against you
because of Jean-Charles.

1302
01:18:24,960 --> 01:18:26,916
What d'you mean?

1303
01:18:27,960 --> 01:18:31,111
Papa promised to give him
my position for the 10%.

1304
01:18:32,160 --> 01:18:34,310
You'll give up your position?
Yes.

1305
01:18:35,720 --> 01:18:40,191
That way, Jean-Charles
will stop travelling and stay here with me.

1306
01:18:44,520 --> 01:18:47,318
I'm no longer able
to live alone.

1307
01:18:48,560 --> 01:18:51,074
I'm pregnant, Mama.

1308
01:18:51,920 --> 01:18:55,708
I'm going on maternity leave
and I'll leave my job.

1309
01:18:56,280 --> 01:18:57,269
It is monstrous.

1310
01:18:57,480 --> 01:19:01,268
You don't have to sacrifice yourself,
 and your work, for your husband.

1311
01:19:01,480 --> 01:19:03,232
And the pill does exist.

1312
01:19:03,440 --> 01:19:07,069
Abortion, too, today.
Jean-Charles is against it.

1313
01:19:07,320 --> 01:19:10,232
But it's your body,
darling.

1314
01:19:10,440 --> 01:19:13,079
It's up to you.

1315
01:19:14,120 --> 01:19:16,395
I made my decision, Mama.

1316
01:19:16,600 --> 01:19:18,830
I want to keep this child.

1317
01:19:21,000 --> 01:19:22,194
Very good.

1318
01:19:23,720 --> 01:19:26,029
I can only rejoice for you.

1319
01:19:26,240 --> 01:19:27,912
I ask one thing:

1320
01:19:28,160 --> 01:19:30,594
Don't get divorced.

1321
01:19:30,840 --> 01:19:33,912
Papa wouldn't support it
and me neither.

1322
01:20:04,913 --> 01:20:06,913
Some months later

1323
01:20:17,160 --> 01:20:19,833
What are you doing?
Nothing.

1324
01:20:20,440 --> 01:20:23,238
Oh, the little rascals.

1325
01:20:25,760 --> 01:20:28,115
 Jean-Charles assured me

1326
01:20:28,320 --> 01:20:29,833
that labor's good in Tunisia .

1327
01:20:30,040 --> 01:20:32,952
There may be workers
for almost nothing.

1328
01:20:33,160 --> 01:20:35,674
We think it'd be
a good idea.

1329
01:20:35,920 --> 01:20:39,913
Suzanne, don't forget
to call the Prefect...

1330
01:20:40,120 --> 01:20:42,475
....Christmas for the kids at the factory.

1331
01:20:42,720 --> 01:20:45,359
I'll ask Mademoiselle Nadège.

1332
01:20:45,560 --> 01:20:47,994
I'll be busy for
the next few days.

1333
01:20:48,240 --> 01:20:49,912
What do you have to do?

1334
01:20:50,160 --> 01:20:51,479
Haven't I told you?

1335
01:20:51,680 --> 01:20:54,990
I am running for election
on an anti-Babin platform.

1336
01:20:58,680 --> 01:20:59,795
Are you crazy?

1337
01:21:00,040 --> 01:21:02,873
No. Just a woman of the 80s.

1338
01:21:03,120 --> 01:21:05,475
Mama, we're still in 1978.

1339
01:21:05,720 --> 01:21:10,236
You've knocked me for living in
the past. Now I'm taking the lead!

1340
01:21:23,800 --> 01:21:25,438
Hello, monsieur.

1341
01:21:25,640 --> 01:21:26,914
I'm Suzanne Pujol.

1342
01:21:27,120 --> 01:21:30,032
Delighted.
I am running for election.

1343
01:21:30,280 --> 01:21:34,068
When I was little, my father
took us to a farm.

1344
01:21:34,280 --> 01:21:36,794
There was one
called Rose.

1345
01:21:37,000 --> 01:21:38,513
"Rose"?

1346
01:21:38,720 --> 01:21:42,349
I have one called Plum
and the other Falbala.

1347
01:21:42,560 --> 01:21:43,595
"Falbala"?

1348
01:21:43,840 --> 01:21:45,956
Is that fermented milk?

1349
01:21:46,160 --> 01:21:48,151
It's milk that's at 37 degrees

1350
01:21:48,360 --> 01:21:51,989
that we mix it with
rennet, and it's is drained.

1351
01:21:52,200 --> 01:21:55,192
Then you put them ...
That's it.

1352
01:21:55,440 --> 01:21:57,954
Chabichou cheese with nettles.

1353
01:21:58,160 --> 01:22:00,276
It is a kind of
Saint-Paulin.

1354
01:22:00,480 --> 01:22:03,995
If I'm elected, I'll support
it at the National Assembly.

1355
01:22:04,200 --> 01:22:06,760
We really need it.

1356
01:22:06,960 --> 01:22:09,315
To you, to us!
Chabichou, it's crazy.

1357
01:22:09,520 --> 01:22:11,033
In Chabrechou!

1358
01:22:15,080 --> 01:22:17,355
Wait. I'm your candidate.

1359
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:20,397
Look, miss.
Thank you.

1360
01:22:20,880 --> 01:22:22,552
Hello, Laurent.
Vote for me.

1361
01:22:22,760 --> 01:22:24,955
Madame Pujol
I'm glad to see you.

1362
01:22:25,160 --> 01:22:28,232
Nadège, how are you?
Oh, it's difficult.

1363
01:22:28,440 --> 01:22:30,431
Everything is back as before.

1364
01:22:30,680 --> 01:22:33,717
Vote for me.
I will improve things.

1365
01:22:33,920 --> 01:22:36,992
I intend to do.
I wanted to tell you one thing.

1366
01:22:37,240 --> 01:22:40,710
What you're doing... it amazes me.
Thank you, Nadège.

1367
01:22:40,960 --> 01:22:45,033
I see that a woman can
succeed without a man.

1368
01:22:45,280 --> 01:22:48,238
I'm Madame Pujol.
I'm running for election.

1369
01:22:48,440 --> 01:22:51,671
I'm for reconciliation
and well-being.

1370
01:22:51,880 --> 01:22:53,916
I'm an independent.

1371
01:22:54,760 --> 01:22:56,637
You spoke to the priest?
Yes.

1372
01:22:56,840 --> 01:22:59,400
He'll vote for us.
That's good.

1373
01:22:59,600 --> 01:23:02,160
He's very influential.
That's true.

1374
01:23:03,160 --> 01:23:05,515
Do I finally
get to meet Floriane?

1375
01:23:05,720 --> 01:23:09,235
No. She's not here.
She doesn't come on weekends?

1376
01:23:09,440 --> 01:23:10,429
It's...over.

1377
01:23:10,680 --> 01:23:13,513
My God!
You told me nothing.

1378
01:23:13,760 --> 01:23:15,955
Not because of me, I hope.

1379
01:23:16,760 --> 01:23:18,113
In a way.

1380
01:23:18,320 --> 01:23:20,993
You're the the most important woman
 in my life.

1381
01:23:21,200 --> 01:23:23,555
You're exaggerating.
I'm just your maman.

1382
01:23:24,520 --> 01:23:25,669
You haven't introduced me to

1383
01:23:25,920 --> 01:23:28,832
that nice young man
who helps us produce the leaflets.

1384
01:23:29,080 --> 01:23:30,274
It's Jean-François.

1385
01:23:30,480 --> 01:23:33,517
He just came along 
and offered to help.

1386
01:23:33,720 --> 01:23:35,073
He adores you too.

1387
01:23:35,320 --> 01:23:39,632
I can understand why people vote
for us seeing this handsome boy.

1388
01:23:39,880 --> 01:23:42,075
You have a family resemblance.

1389
01:23:42,280 --> 01:23:44,953
He's Monsieur Balestra the notary's son
.

1390
01:23:46,320 --> 01:23:48,595
Your father will be pleased.
About what?

1391
01:23:48,800 --> 01:23:51,633
That you've broken up
with Floriane...

1392
01:23:51,840 --> 01:23:54,877
His snobbishness about his son with a pastrycook ...

1393
01:23:55,120 --> 01:23:56,997
Here, Jacqueline.

1394
01:23:57,640 --> 01:24:00,029
March 12,
Vote for Madame Pujol.

1395
01:24:00,240 --> 01:24:02,959
You never go out,
but there, it's worth it.

1396
01:24:04,000 --> 01:24:06,150
Ah, Nadège.
Hello. Going OK?

1397
01:24:07,920 --> 01:24:10,798
You want to get rid of Babin?
Now's the time.

1398
01:24:11,040 --> 01:24:13,235
Vote Babin. March 12.

1399
01:24:13,880 --> 01:24:17,350
Your father, okay?
Have him come March 12.

1400
01:24:17,560 --> 01:24:19,516
Hello. Feeling well?

1401
01:24:19,720 --> 01:24:22,029
Remember
March 12, vote Babin.

1402
01:24:22,960 --> 01:24:25,838
Very good cheese.
March 12, at the polls.

1403
01:24:27,920 --> 01:24:29,672
Thank you. Hello to your wife.

1404
01:24:30,480 --> 01:24:32,118
What's this?

1405
01:24:36,440 --> 01:24:38,237
Ah, that Pujol woman.

1406
01:24:42,040 --> 01:24:44,873
Pass out leaflets, the leaflets!
Babin ...Vote Babin!

1407
01:24:45,120 --> 01:24:48,237
Hello, sir.
I consider everyone.

1408
01:24:48,480 --> 01:24:51,756
She's had a facelift.
She had to go on a diet.

1409
01:24:53,280 --> 01:24:54,918
Hello.
Hello, Madame Pujol.

1410
01:24:55,120 --> 01:24:57,793
Hello.
Good luck.

1411
01:24:58,640 --> 01:25:02,189
Madame Pujol, you recognize me?
No.

1412
01:25:02,440 --> 01:25:05,193
I worked 40 years
for your dad.

1413
01:25:05,400 --> 01:25:07,470
He loved me very much.

1414
01:25:07,720 --> 01:25:09,358
Oh yeah?
You know,

1415
01:25:09,600 --> 01:25:10,715
I had 11 children.

1416
01:25:10,960 --> 01:25:14,032
11 children!
They've all worked at the factory.

1417
01:25:14,280 --> 01:25:18,592
Thank you for what you did
for me and my family.

1418
01:25:18,840 --> 01:25:19,909
But it's nothing.

1419
01:25:20,160 --> 01:25:21,036
Goodbye.

1420
01:25:21,240 --> 01:25:23,231
March 12.
I'm counting on you.

1421
01:25:23,480 --> 01:25:25,072
Vote Suzanne Pujol.

1422
01:25:32,520 --> 01:25:36,149
Is that you, bitch, spreading
propaganda in my factory?

1423
01:25:36,360 --> 01:25:39,033
I'd never do
such a thing...

1424
01:25:39,240 --> 01:25:41,629
to go against
your interests!

1425
01:25:41,840 --> 01:25:44,593
If I find out that you're 
the eye of Moscow

1426
01:25:44,800 --> 01:25:45,869
you'll be fired.

1427
01:25:46,080 --> 01:25:49,834
The tribunal will be delighted
to accept my secrets

1428
01:25:50,040 --> 01:25:52,190
about the factory's operations.

1429
01:26:01,240 --> 01:26:02,912
I'm not disturbing you, Suzanne?

1430
01:26:03,160 --> 01:26:05,594
No. I'm finishing reading
this report.

1431
01:26:05,840 --> 01:26:07,831
It's crazy:
They want to scrap

1432
01:26:08,080 --> 01:26:09,798
the Saint-Amand-les-Eaux road

1433
01:26:10,960 --> 01:26:12,552
Can I sleep with you?

1434
01:26:13,240 --> 01:26:14,639
What's got into you?

1435
01:26:16,960 --> 01:26:20,839
Listen, I'm still working...
...and you and I are divorcing.

1436
01:26:21,080 --> 01:26:24,231
It will complicate things.

1437
01:26:24,480 --> 01:26:27,790
You're such a pet.
Why don't you go to the 'Bada-Boom'?

1438
01:26:28,040 --> 01:26:30,913
It's closed on Thursdays.

1439
01:26:30,914 --> 01:26:34,114
Just a kiss, then go to sleep.


1440
01:26:49,680 --> 01:26:53,468
What are you thinking?
About us.

1441
01:26:54,880 --> 01:26:57,792
An old story.
No.

1442
01:26:59,360 --> 01:27:02,193
Remember our honeymoon?

1443
01:27:03,120 --> 01:27:07,830
I remember a wild beach
in the depths of Brittany.

1444
01:27:09,360 --> 01:27:12,557
It was a deserted cove.

1445
01:27:14,400 --> 01:27:16,789
The sun was setting.

1446
01:27:17,680 --> 01:27:20,035
The sea was cool.

1447
01:27:20,920 --> 01:27:23,514
She seemed so hot
in your arms.

1448
01:27:23,720 --> 01:27:26,314
It seemed so blue
in your eyes.

1449
01:27:26,520 --> 01:27:30,069
We were young, beautiful,
heedless.

1450
01:27:30,880 --> 01:27:32,996
We loved each other.

1451
01:27:37,320 --> 01:27:40,039
Why divorce
after all these years?

1452
01:27:40,240 --> 01:27:42,674
What's the point?

1453
01:27:43,320 --> 01:27:45,550
So you'll look at me
differently.

1454
01:27:45,760 --> 01:27:48,513
I do look at you differently.

1455
01:27:49,480 --> 01:27:52,517
Tell me something, Robert?
Will you vote for me?

1456
01:27:56,360 --> 01:28:00,114
Joëlle Hersant.
Voted.

1457
01:28:00,320 --> 01:28:03,949
Hubert Barbin.
Voted.

1458
01:28:04,160 --> 01:28:05,309
Madame Pilar Sanchez.

1459
01:28:06,840 --> 01:28:07,909
Voted.

1460
01:28:08,120 --> 01:28:10,350
Madame Gilberte Pacot.

1461
01:28:10,560 --> 01:28:13,632
André Ferron.
Voted.

1462
01:28:13,840 --> 01:28:16,229
Monsieur Babin!
So how did it go?

1463
01:28:17,640 --> 01:28:19,312
Maurice Babin.

1464
01:28:20,560 --> 01:28:22,278
Voted.

1465
01:28:23,800 --> 01:28:24,949
Monsieur Babin

1466
01:28:25,160 --> 01:28:29,199
what are your predictions?
Listen, I'm confident.

1467
01:28:29,720 --> 01:28:31,870
Geneviève Michonneau.

1468
01:28:32,080 --> 01:28:35,595
Mademoiselle Dumoulin Nadège.

1469
01:28:36,320 --> 01:28:39,198
Robert Pujol.
Voted.

1470
01:28:40,120 --> 01:28:42,475
Going well?
Yes. An upset.

1471
01:28:42,680 --> 01:28:44,272
An upset?

1472
01:28:44,480 --> 01:28:46,471
Madame Joelle Pujol de Morette.

1473
01:28:48,880 --> 01:28:49,630
Voted.

1474
01:28:52,720 --> 01:28:55,473
I hope that you will win.
Thank you.

1475
01:28:57,320 --> 01:28:59,390
Hello, Madame Pujol.

1476
01:28:59,600 --> 01:29:00,874
Hello.

1477
01:29:02,600 --> 01:29:06,275
Suzanne Pujol.
Voted.

1478
01:29:10,880 --> 01:29:13,474
Your predictions?
No comment.

1479
01:29:25,000 --> 01:29:27,878
Final results are in, mother.

1480
01:29:31,600 --> 01:29:33,511
Leave me alone for a moment?

1481
01:29:33,720 --> 01:29:34,914
Sure.

1482
01:29:39,400 --> 01:29:41,960
Hello?

1483
01:29:42,960 --> 01:29:44,234
Good evening, Madame Pujol.

1484
01:29:44,480 --> 01:29:47,074
You've got the result?

1485
01:29:47,280 --> 01:29:48,315
Yes

1486
01:29:48,560 --> 01:29:51,393
Why?
You've not stuffed the ballot boxes.

1487
01:29:51,640 --> 01:29:54,950
Seriously,
you're not too disappointed?

1488
01:29:55,200 --> 01:29:56,633
Not as much as your husband.

1489
01:29:56,880 --> 01:29:59,440
You think so?

1490
01:29:59,680 --> 01:30:03,878
Your real opponent
it was not me but him.

1491
01:30:04,880 --> 01:30:06,916
Maybe.

1492
01:30:07,120 --> 01:30:08,872
We can stay friends?

1493
01:30:09,120 --> 01:30:13,557
Your new position 'll
make us meet often.

1494
01:30:13,760 --> 01:30:15,273
Of course

1495
01:30:15,480 --> 01:30:17,596
Mostly face-to-face.

1496
01:30:17,800 --> 01:30:19,438
I look forward to it.

1497
01:30:19,640 --> 01:30:20,390
Maman,

1498
01:30:20,600 --> 01:30:22,716
people are beginning to arrive.

1499
01:30:22,920 --> 01:30:27,675
Excuse me, I must go.
See you soon, Madame Deputy.

1500
01:30:27,880 --> 01:30:30,348
Very soon, Monsieur Le ...
...Monsieur Mayor.

1501
01:30:49,320 --> 01:30:50,309
Please.

1502
01:30:51,560 --> 01:30:54,279
Good evening, everybody.
Thank you for being here.

1503
01:30:54,520 --> 01:30:58,877
I ask you kindly
welcome our new parliamentary deputy,

1504
01:30:59,120 --> 01:31:01,270
Suzanne Pujol!

1505
01:31:06,840 --> 01:31:08,398
Good evening.

1506
01:31:09,560 --> 01:31:11,710
SUZANNE! SUZANNE! SUZANNE!

1507
01:31:11,960 --> 01:31:15,873
My friends, let me first
thank you

1508
01:31:16,080 --> 01:31:18,833
for electing me in the first round.

1509
01:31:20,160 --> 01:31:23,277
I also want to offer,
in all fraternity ...

1510
01:31:23,520 --> 01:31:26,796
We won! We won!

1511
01:31:27,040 --> 01:31:29,031
Yes, we won.

1512
01:31:29,280 --> 01:31:32,033
I also want to offer
in all brotherhood

1513
01:31:32,240 --> 01:31:35,596
all my respect to our mayor, 
Maurice Babin


1514
01:31:35,840 --> 01:31:39,071
and all my friends too.

1515
01:31:40,120 --> 01:31:42,270
In this moving victory night

1516
01:31:42,480 --> 01:31:45,870
I can only have but an emotional thought
for my father

1517
01:31:46,120 --> 01:31:49,829
who would have been so proud of his daughter.

1518
01:31:50,080 --> 01:31:53,755
And it is in his memory
I solemnly declare that I want

1519
01:31:53,960 --> 01:31:56,030
me, Suzanne Pujol
born a Michonneau,

1520
